Roger Federer Reaches U.S. Open 4th Round with Four-Set Win Against Cilic

-- B y   R o b   G l o s t e r
-- 
2011-09-03T20:00:11Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-03/roger-federer-reaches-u-s-open-4th-round-with-four-set-win-against-cilic.html
Five-time champion  Roger Federer 
advanced to the fourth round of the U.S. Open with a four-set
victory today against Marin Cilic, the 27th seed from  Croatia .  Federer, 30, the third seed from  Switzerland , won 6-3, 4-6,
6-4, 6-2 in a match at Arthur Ashe Stadium that took 2 hours, 40
minutes. He will play either Juan Monaco of  Argentina  or Tommy
Haas of  Germany  in the fourth round.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Rob Gloster at 
 rgloster@bloomberg.net  